  <chapter id="specifictest"><title>Specific Office Productivity Applications</title>

    <section id="desktoptest"><title>Desktop Test Plan</title>
      <section><title>Navigate Start Menu</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads the top level of the start menu.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the start menu from the keyboard and arrow up and down through all the items.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When first entering the menu orca should speak the name of the panel gaining focus.  Orca should speak the selected item  while arrowing.  If an item is a submenu, orca should fillow the item name with "menu".</para>
                <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads correctly when entering submenus.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the start menu and navigate into each of the submenus..</para>
        <para>&tresult; When moving into the submenu orca should speak the new item with focus.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads correctly when leaving submenus.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the start menu and navigate into each of the submenus with right arrow and then return to the ptop level with left arrow.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When moving out of the submmenu orca should speak the new item with focus.</para>
<para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads and navigates the top and bottom panels.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Press CTRL+ALT+tab to get to the desktop.  Press this combination again to get to the top panel with the varius status bottons.  Press space on each button.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When arrowing to each pannel applet orca should read it and it's status.  When activating it orca should read any changes the user makes in the dialog.</para>
      </section>
      <section><title>Alt+Tab to Other Applications</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads metacity status window.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open gedit, terminal, star office writer, and firefox.  With these apps opened, hold sown alt and press tab slowly several times.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Whith each press of tab orca should speak the name of the application that will gain fucus if als is released.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section id="nautilustest"><title>Nautilus Test Plan</title>
      <section><title>File list navigation</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if orca reads the file names and the folder names..</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Go to the places menu and open your home folder.  Down arrow to each item in the list.  At the end of the list reverse direction back to the top.</para>
        <para>&tresult; As each item is selected its name should be spoken.  If the item is a folder the expanded or collapsed state should also be spoken.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads column changes.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the home folder.  Down arrow to several items.  On each item right and left arrow across the various columns.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Orca should read the column header as well as the value of the current cell.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads the opening of new folders.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the home folder.  Down arrow to a folder and press enter.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Orca should read the value of the newly selected cell.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads the toolbar buttons.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open the home folder.  Tab to the toolbar and arrow to all the buttons.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Orca should read the label for each button.</para>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section id="gedittest"><title>GEdit Test Plan</title>
      <section><title>Toolbar and menubar test</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if orca reads the menubar and the sub menus.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Press F10 and right arrow across the menubar.  When reaching the help menu left arrow back to the file menu.  On the file menu down arrow to all the choices.</para>
        <para>&tresult; On the menubar orca should read each item followed by "menu".  When navigating the file menu orca should read each item followed by "..." if that item contains more options.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if orca properly navigates the toolbar in flat review.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Use KP7 to move up to the toolbar.  Press KP6 to move to each toolbar item.  On each button press KP/ to activate the button.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Orca should read each button and when clicked with KP/ the appropriate action should be taken.</para>
      </section>
      <section><title>Dialog box test</title>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca correctly reads the "file open" dialog.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Open gedit and only using the arrows and enter navigate to the Change.log under your orca sub directory.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When traversing the directory structure orca should read each item telling the user if it is a file or folder.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads the find dialog.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Press CTRL+f to bring up the find dialog.  Type "Mike" and press enter.</para>
        <para>&tresult; When the find dialog comes up it should be read.  When enter is pressed on Mike orca should speak that the word has been found.</para>
        <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca reads the "quit without saving dialog.</para>
        <para>&tprocedure; Delete the word Mike found in the last test and press CTRL+q.</para>
        <para>&tresult; Orca should speak the dialog warning the user that the changes will be lost.</para>
      </section>
            <section><title> spell check test</title>
              <para>&tgoal; Determine if Orca correctly reads the spell check test.</para>
              <para>&tprocedure; Open the orca change log in gedit and press F7 to open the spell checker.  Spell check several words.</para>
              <para>&tresult; When each word is flagged it should be spoken followed by the surrounding context.</para>
      </section>
      </section>

